@emss/jest-mock-console is only used in tests, so yes for that one.

I checked the exported dts and saw that EMSSUser is still imported from @emss/oauth2-proxy-common, so I added it back to dependencies. I did not realize it would not get bundled in the dts.

I also saw Request and Response types imported from express (@types/request) so I added it as a peerDependency so it should resolve correctly now.

Comparison: [@emss/logger@0.7.1...@emss/logger@0.8.2](https://eegitlab.fit.nasa.gov/emss/packages/-/compare/@emss%2Flogger@0.7.1...@emss%2Flogger@0.8.2?from_project_id=685)

Added lines: <https://eegitlab.fit.nasa.gov/emss/packages/-/compare/@emss%2Flogger@0.7.1...@emss%2Flogger@0.8.2?from_project_id=685#line_5ed6dd63a_A225>

